Pour the @water for the rice{300%ml} into a #medium saucepan{} with a
tight-fitting #lid{}.

Stir in the @Basmati Rice{150%g} and @salt{1/4%tsp} and bring to the boil. Once
boiling, turn the heat down to medium and cover with the lid.

Leave to cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove the pan from the heat (still
covered) and leave to the side for another ~{10%minutes} or until ready to
serve (the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

Meanwhile, halve the @Bell Pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Chop into
1cm chunks.

Trim and thinly slice the @Spring Onion{2}. Crush the @Salted Peanuts{25%g} in
the unopened sachet using a #rolling pin{}. Drain the
@King Prawns{150%g}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw prawns.

When the rice has 10 mins remaining, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a
#large frying pan{} on high heat.

Once hot, add the pepper chunks and fry until just soft, ~{3-4%minutes}.
Continue to stir while it cooks.

Once the pepper has softened, add the prawns and half the spring onion to the
pan.

Stir-fry until the prawns are cooked through, ~{4-5%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The prawns are cooked when pink on the outside and opaque in the
> middle.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @olive oil{} in a #medium frying pan{} on
medium-high heat.

Once hot, crack in each @Egg{2} (1 per person) and cook for ~{4-5%minutes}, or
until the egg white is cooked and the yolk is the firmness you desire. Lower
the heat as needed.

> IMPORTANT: Ensure egg whites are fully cooked.

Once the prawns are cooked, add the @Ginger, Garlic & Lemongrass Puree{15%g}.
Stir-fry until fragrant, ~{1%minute}.

Stir in the cooked rice, @Peas{120%g}, @Soy Sauce{25%ml} and
@Sambal Paste{15%g} (add less if you'd prefer things milder). Cook until
piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if needed. Add a splash of water if
it's a little dry. Remove from the heat.

Share the fried rice between your #bowls{}.

Top with the fried egg.

Scatter over the peanuts and remaining spring onion to finish.

Enjoy!